         <div type="entry" xml:id="lc.jrn.1805-10-06.03" n="">
            <sp who="jo">
               <speaker>Ordway</speaker>
               <ab>
                  <date/>
               </ab>
               <p>
Sunday 6th Oct 1805.    a pleasant morning.    a hole or carsh dug hide our pack Saddles in.    we got oars and poles ready.    towards evening we got the other canoes ready to put in the river. Some gig poles got ready.    an Indian raft seen floating down the <name type="place" key="Clearwater (Flathead, Kooskooskee) River">koskoskia River</name>.    one of the men killed two ducks.    after night burryed the pack Saddles &amp;C.—


</p>
            </sp>
